1
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:14,200
<i>Everything about her,
it's just different.</i>

2
00:00:14,333 --> 00:00:16,800
<i>She's no longer the Emma
I used to know.</i>

3
00:00:16,933 --> 00:00:17,800
<i> Mookie, Stacy!</i>

4
00:00:17,933 --> 00:00:21,000
<i>- Enough!
- Mookie!</i>

5
00:00:21,133 --> 00:00:23,900
<i>Mookie! You can never get near
my niece again!</i>

6
00:00:24,033 --> 00:00:24,900
<i> I'm grounded?</i>

7
00:00:25,033 --> 00:00:26,600
<i> Go! Get inside!</i>

8
00:00:26,733 --> 00:00:29,167
<i>You can still do
whatever you want.</i>

9
00:00:29,300 --> 00:00:32,433
<i>I think this is the right time
to confront Jade.</i>

10
00:00:32,567 --> 00:00:34,967
<i>They want to book
the bar for an event.</i>

11
00:00:35,133 --> 00:00:36,700
<i> Haven't you still found Emma?</i>

12
00:00:36,833 --> 00:00:37,700
<i> I'm sorry.</i>

13
00:00:37,833 --> 00:00:39,233
<i> I didn't get a lead.</i>

14
00:00:39,367 --> 00:00:40,267
<i>- Jade.
- Give the kid a break.</i>

15
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:43,100
<i>It's my fault she's behaving
like that.</i>

16
00:00:43,233 --> 00:00:44,100
<i> Leticia?</i>

17
00:00:44,233 --> 00:00:45,333
<i> What are you doing here?</i>

18
00:00:45,467 --> 00:00:48,500
<i>You betrayed me when I needed
someone on my side!</i>

19
00:00:48,633 --> 00:00:49,467
<i> Left behind?</i>

20
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:50,467
<i>What are you talking about,
Jade?</i>

21
00:00:50,600 --> 00:00:53,633
<i>But you can't stand up
by your word.</i>

22
00:00:53,767 --> 00:00:54,767
<i> Olive?</i>

23
00:01:33,733 --> 00:01:34,700
Are you okay?

24
00:01:34,833 --> 00:01:37,233
Boss, I'll get you ice.

25
00:01:37,367 --> 00:01:39,067
Wait.

26
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:40,667
No.

27
00:01:40,833 --> 00:01:43,667
- I'm okay. Good.
- Sorry, sorry.

28
00:01:50,300 --> 00:01:55,367
Maybe we should continue this
tomorrow.

29
00:01:55,500 --> 00:02:00,033
Let's first plan what we're
going to do to scare Jade.

30
00:02:01,500 --> 00:02:02,600
What plan?

31
00:02:05,300 --> 00:02:09,633
Jade panicked when she saw you,
remember?

32
00:02:09,767 --> 00:02:13,033
She seemed like she saw a ghost.

33
00:02:14,833 --> 00:02:16,633
That's what you'll do.

34
00:02:16,767 --> 00:02:18,133
Remember, Emma.

35
00:02:18,267 --> 00:02:21,833
This is the actual war.

36
00:02:23,467 --> 00:02:26,333
This is the real battle,
not just a fistfight.

37
00:02:28,300 --> 00:02:29,333
It's a war of the mind.

38
00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:39,367
Your most powerful weapon
is not a gun but her fear.

39
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:42,433
When you instill fear
in the enemy,

40
00:02:42,567 --> 00:02:44,267
all her plans and actions
will fail.

41
00:02:44,400 --> 00:02:50,600
It's as if she can't even
trust her own shadow.

42
00:02:50,767 --> 00:02:53,967
That's one of the strategies
to win.

43
00:02:54,100 --> 00:02:56,333
Weaken the enemy's defense.

44
00:02:57,767 --> 00:03:04,367
But if you get caught,
you'll just become a joke.

45
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:08,800
So when you attack,
you need to be like a shadow.

46
00:03:08,933 --> 00:03:09,900
Boss, ice.

47
00:03:12,267 --> 00:03:13,267
I don't need that.

48
00:03:20,500 --> 00:03:23,433
I know what to do to avoid
getting caught by Jade.

49
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:24,667
Good.

50
00:03:28,567 --> 00:03:30,667
Of course not, you idiot.

51
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:32,367
I'm Jade.

52
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:38,600
I only heard your useless
promise from Olive.

53
00:03:38,733 --> 00:03:40,700
Stop denying it, Olive.

54
00:03:40,833 --> 00:03:41,833
That's our secret code,

55
00:03:41,967 --> 00:03:44,600
so I don't get confused between
you and Jade.

56
00:03:47,533 --> 00:03:50,067
I say back to back,
soul to soul.

57
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:53,300
And you say never apart.

58
00:03:53,433 --> 00:03:54,467
All again.

59
00:03:54,633 --> 00:03:55,933
Olive, you're alive!

60
00:03:56,067 --> 00:03:58,533
Keep quiet!

61
00:03:58,667 --> 00:04:02,033
Don't tell anyone my secret.

62
00:04:02,167 --> 00:04:05,833
I'll kill you if you do.

63
00:04:05,967 --> 00:04:08,867
You can slap me
all you want, Olive.

64
00:04:10,833 --> 00:04:12,100
If that will make you
forgive me.

65
00:04:13,900 --> 00:04:16,500
I hid for a long time
because I was wanted.

66
00:04:16,633 --> 00:04:19,267
Because of the drugs
I was supplying.

67
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:23,467
But now, I can move freely.

68
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:25,100
I have a new partner.

69
00:04:26,367 --> 00:04:27,367
City councilor.

70
00:04:29,033 --> 00:04:30,500
He's the one protecting me.

71
00:04:32,233 --> 00:04:34,233
But, Olive, you were never
out of my mind.

72
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:38,433
You are my only true friend.

73
00:04:39,700 --> 00:04:41,600
You are the only one
I can rely on...

74
00:04:42,833 --> 00:04:43,800
like a family.

75
00:04:46,467 --> 00:04:47,567
So, I'm sorry.

76
00:04:49,867 --> 00:04:50,700
Fine.

77
00:04:52,467 --> 00:04:54,833
You were the only ally I had.

78
00:04:56,533 --> 00:04:57,700
You were my only family.

79
00:04:58,967 --> 00:05:00,067
Olive, wait.

80
00:05:01,533 --> 00:05:03,300
Why are you pretending
to be Jade?

81
00:05:05,933 --> 00:05:07,300
Fine.

82
00:05:07,433 --> 00:05:09,133
I will tell you everything.

83
00:05:11,633 --> 00:05:12,700
Please.

84
00:05:23,133 --> 00:05:26,333
So that's all that happened
to me when you were away.

85
00:05:27,667 --> 00:05:31,067
Disaster after disaster.

86
00:05:34,367 --> 00:05:38,200
Olive, I didn't know you went
through all those hardships.

87
00:05:38,333 --> 00:05:40,400
I wasn't by your side
when it all happened.

88
00:05:42,967 --> 00:05:43,933
I'll make it up to you.

89
00:05:45,167 --> 00:05:48,667
Tell me what to do
so you can forgive me, Olive.

90
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:49,767
Anything?

91
00:05:55,433 --> 00:05:56,467
Okay.

92
00:05:57,500 --> 00:05:59,033
I'll take your offer on that.

93
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:02,800
Find Emma.

94
00:06:02,933 --> 00:06:03,867
Is that all?

95
00:06:05,100 --> 00:06:06,533
That simple?

96
00:06:06,667 --> 00:06:07,933
It'll be easy.

97
00:06:08,100 --> 00:06:09,600
I have lots of connections.

98
00:06:26,067 --> 00:06:27,767
Mookie?

99
00:06:27,900 --> 00:06:28,700
<i> Dear?</i>

100
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:36,433
You haven't eaten all day.

101
00:06:36,567 --> 00:06:38,867
You might get sick.

102
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:40,600
I'm not hungry.

103
00:06:40,767 --> 00:06:43,133
And I don't want to talk to you.

104
00:06:43,267 --> 00:06:44,300
So, please.

105
00:06:45,733 --> 00:06:49,933
I'll leave the food outside
in case you get hungry.

106
00:06:51,700 --> 00:06:54,300
Fine. Do what you want.

107
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:24,833
Mookie, let's talk, please.
I'm worried for you.

108
00:07:27,367 --> 00:07:30,767
<i>I don't need your worry
and pity.</i>

109
00:07:30,900 --> 00:07:34,167
<i>I'm no longer the old Mookie
who's a damsel in distress.</i>

110
00:07:34,300 --> 00:07:35,967
<i> I'm a fighter now.</i>

111
00:07:36,100 --> 00:07:37,833
<i> I can manage on my own.</i>

112
00:07:37,967 --> 00:07:39,633
<i> I don't need you guys anymore.</i>

113
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,033
<i> There.</i>

114
00:07:49,167 --> 00:07:51,400
<i> I'm even feeding you.</i>

115
00:07:51,533 --> 00:07:52,833
<i> One more.</i>

116
00:07:52,967 --> 00:07:54,400
I'm going to talk to Danilo.

117
00:07:54,533 --> 00:07:55,833
Me, too!

118
00:07:55,967 --> 00:07:57,667
Kutsy, Wiro.

119
00:07:57,800 --> 00:07:58,900
Danilo.

120
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:02,233
Loida, thank you.

121
00:08:02,367 --> 00:08:03,567
How are you?

122
00:08:03,700 --> 00:08:05,800
- We're already eating.
- Kutsy, Wiro. Go on.

123
00:08:05,933 --> 00:08:07,400
- Have a seat.
- Sit.

124
00:08:07,533 --> 00:08:09,067
Let's sit.

125
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:12,200
What is this that I heard?

126
00:08:12,333 --> 00:08:13,867
Danilo,

127
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:16,567
don't let your misunderstanding
with Mookie worsen.

128
00:08:17,967 --> 00:08:20,233
You only have each other.

129
00:08:20,367 --> 00:08:21,500
I know.

130
00:08:23,100 --> 00:08:27,800
But Jade is there to mediate
and help us reconcile.

131
00:08:28,933 --> 00:08:32,533
Seems like Jade has truly
replaced Emma's spot

132
00:08:32,667 --> 00:08:34,400
in your life, doesn't it?

133
00:08:38,300 --> 00:08:40,200
No one can replace Emma.

134
00:08:41,633 --> 00:08:46,033
Everything would be fine
if only she returned to us.

135
00:08:48,967 --> 00:08:51,300
Let me talk to him.

136
00:08:51,433 --> 00:08:52,467
Classic you.

137
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:56,933
We really don't know
what happened.

138
00:08:57,100 --> 00:08:59,433
Who knows?
Maybe she had an accident.

139
00:08:59,567 --> 00:09:02,000
And she had an amnesia.

140
00:09:02,133 --> 00:09:03,333
- Right?
- Yes.

141
00:09:03,467 --> 00:09:05,900
So don't lose hope.

142
00:09:06,033 --> 00:09:07,200
- Move, move, move.
- Ouch.

143
00:09:09,533 --> 00:09:12,767
But how's your search?

144
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:14,833
There's still no lead.

145
00:09:16,300 --> 00:09:18,300
Poor Mookie.

146
00:09:18,433 --> 00:09:19,300
She has no mother.

147
00:09:19,433 --> 00:09:22,600
And her grandmother
is missing in action.

148
00:09:22,733 --> 00:09:26,033
Don't you hear anything
from Mommy Ligaya?

149
00:09:26,167 --> 00:09:28,733
She still hasn't contacted me.

150
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:32,767
Well, there hasn't been
any sign from her either.

151
00:09:34,233 --> 00:09:36,467
Even just a whiff of a candle

152
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:38,233
or the scent of Sampaguita
would have been nice.

153
00:09:38,367 --> 00:09:41,333
But I only have goosebumps
whenever I'm in the restroom.

154
00:09:41,467 --> 00:09:42,700
Nothing.

155
00:09:42,833 --> 00:09:44,500
How about Jade?

156
00:09:44,633 --> 00:09:46,167
Jade?

157
00:09:46,300 --> 00:09:47,333
Oh no.

158
00:09:51,733 --> 00:09:52,733
<i> God,</i>

159
00:09:54,133 --> 00:09:56,333
<i>please help me escape from here!</i>

160
00:09:57,800 --> 00:09:59,200
<i> I'm begging you.</i>

161
00:10:03,567 --> 00:10:04,567
<i> What was that?</i>

162
00:10:07,633 --> 00:10:08,867
<i> Did you hear that?</i>

163
00:10:10,333 --> 00:10:11,867
<i> I also did.</i>

164
00:10:14,133 --> 00:10:16,100
It seems like it's coming
from there.

165
00:10:16,233 --> 00:10:18,000
Over there.

166
00:10:18,133 --> 00:10:20,067
Danilo, does this house
have a basement?

167
00:10:21,667 --> 00:10:22,633
Yes, Wiro. It does have.

168
00:10:23,900 --> 00:10:25,300
I also hear it sometimes.

169
00:10:25,433 --> 00:10:27,467
That's why I want
to check that noise.

170
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:29,767
- Then let's check it!
- Come on!

171
00:10:29,900 --> 00:10:32,667
There are lots of rats
in our basement.

172
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:35,833
I forget to call exterminators.

173
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:37,333
Hi friends!

174
00:10:37,467 --> 00:10:40,467
- Hey, Jade!
- I'm glad you came to visit.

175
00:10:40,600 --> 00:10:41,833
Yeah, yeah.

176
00:10:41,967 --> 00:10:45,100
We only came to see
Danilo and Mookie.

177
00:10:45,233 --> 00:10:47,100
- Yeah, yeah.
- Oh, really?

178
00:10:47,233 --> 00:10:48,433
How sweet of you.

179
00:10:49,667 --> 00:10:50,600
But don't worry,

180
00:10:50,733 --> 00:10:53,133
I take good care of my husband
and kid.

181
00:10:53,267 --> 00:10:54,033
Right, love?

182
00:10:55,433 --> 00:10:57,000
So much, right?

183
00:10:57,133 --> 00:10:59,233
Danilo told us about it.

184
00:10:59,367 --> 00:11:00,833
He's very well taken care of.

185
00:11:00,967 --> 00:11:02,833
How about Ligaya?

186
00:11:02,967 --> 00:11:05,167
Do you have a news update
about her?

187
00:11:05,300 --> 00:11:06,433
Mom?

188
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:09,333
I don't.

189
00:11:09,467 --> 00:11:11,633
But I'm sure Mom is okay.

190
00:11:11,767 --> 00:11:13,067
Have a seat.

191
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:17,333
Go on. Have some snacks.
Please, eat. Go ahead, go ahead.

192
00:11:17,467 --> 00:11:21,133
- We're actually leaving.
- There's a tournament.

193
00:11:21,267 --> 00:11:23,700
- Yes, yes.
- We have a Tong-its tournament.

194
00:11:23,833 --> 00:11:25,800
Yes, yes.

195
00:11:25,933 --> 00:11:26,800
So, we'll get going.

196
00:11:27,833 --> 00:11:29,967
Good luck to your tournament!

197
00:11:30,100 --> 00:11:31,967
- Thank you.
- Love, will you see them out?

198
00:11:32,100 --> 00:11:33,433
Sure. Let's go, Wiro.

199
00:11:33,567 --> 00:11:36,100
- Don't forget your bag.
- Loida, please see them out.

200
00:11:36,233 --> 00:11:37,800
No, it's all good.

201
00:11:37,933 --> 00:11:40,000
- We'll be careful.
- Be safe.

202
00:11:40,133 --> 00:11:42,167
Thanks for dropping by.

203
00:11:42,333 --> 00:11:43,900
Are you sure you don't want
to stay?

204
00:11:44,033 --> 00:11:47,267
- No, we're good.
- Thanks for the food.

205
00:12:17,067 --> 00:12:18,500
What are you doing?

206
00:12:21,500 --> 00:12:23,967
Did you drop the chair
to make a noise?

207
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:27,733
Is that your strategy, Ligaya?

208
00:12:30,633 --> 00:12:33,533
Well, sadly, it's not working.

209
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:36,400
The sound you made seemed like

210
00:12:36,533 --> 00:12:38,000
a bunch of mice
chasing each other.

211
00:12:39,167 --> 00:12:40,400
Nobody cares.

212
00:12:42,133 --> 00:12:43,633
Oh, yeah.

213
00:12:48,833 --> 00:12:49,900
Are you already hungry?

214
00:12:50,933 --> 00:12:55,700
Sorry, I haven't fed you
for two days.

215
00:12:57,133 --> 00:12:58,967
I got busy.

216
00:12:59,100 --> 00:13:00,267
But don't worry.

217
00:13:01,700 --> 00:13:04,033
I bought you something
delicious.

218
00:13:05,433 --> 00:13:06,500
You'll love it.

219
00:13:12,100 --> 00:13:13,700
Oh, I forgot.

220
00:13:13,833 --> 00:13:15,833
You can't eat.

221
00:13:17,267 --> 00:13:18,300
There.

222
00:13:18,433 --> 00:13:19,533
You can eat now.

223
00:13:21,767 --> 00:13:24,500
Please stop.
Let me out.

224
00:13:27,067 --> 00:13:28,533
Don't be so dramatic.

225
00:13:30,967 --> 00:13:32,900
You only got hungry,

226
00:13:36,167 --> 00:13:38,733
unlike what you did to us.

227
00:13:40,467 --> 00:13:46,067
You deprived us of love.

228
00:13:47,700 --> 00:13:49,033
That's not true.

229
00:13:50,867 --> 00:13:53,867
How often do I have to tell you?

230
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:59,000
I was only thinking about
your and Jade's welfare.

231
00:14:00,067 --> 00:14:06,267
We would all have died of hunger
if I hadn't given you away.

232
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:09,700
And I also didn't want you
to experience

233
00:14:09,833 --> 00:14:12,900
what I went through
with your father.

234
00:14:13,033 --> 00:14:14,267
He was abusive.

235
00:14:14,400 --> 00:14:16,633
I didn't want him
to hurt you, too.

236
00:14:18,100 --> 00:14:19,400
When you gave us up
for adoption,

237
00:14:21,267 --> 00:14:25,600
did you even check if the people
who adopted us were nice?

238
00:14:27,167 --> 00:14:29,700
Or did you just throw us
to them?

239
00:14:29,867 --> 00:14:31,000
Dear.

240
00:14:32,833 --> 00:14:35,733
Dear, I'm begging you.

241
00:14:35,867 --> 00:14:36,933
Shut up!

242
00:14:39,533 --> 00:14:42,700
Your tears will never work
on me.

243
00:14:46,667 --> 00:14:52,667
Eat before I put a gag back
in your mouth.

244
00:15:40,967 --> 00:15:44,000
What will you do
if Jade strangles you?

245
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:47,033
What will you do?

246
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:50,967
What will you do?

247
00:15:53,700 --> 00:15:54,933
Presence of mind.

248
00:15:55,067 --> 00:15:58,867
I should be alert.

249
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,200
Right.

250
00:16:01,067 --> 00:16:05,767
Because your first reaction
is to panic.

251
00:16:09,900 --> 00:16:14,033
The first thing you should do
is to step on her foot.

252
00:16:14,167 --> 00:16:15,233
Try it.

253
00:16:16,900 --> 00:16:17,900
Not that way.

254
00:16:20,133 --> 00:16:26,467
You should give it all
your strength when you do it.

255
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:30,000
You will use the anger
you feel towards Jade.

256
00:16:30,133 --> 00:16:33,400
In a fight,
you must strike first.

257
00:16:35,067 --> 00:16:37,667
You should hit her hard.

258
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:40,300
Because it's a race
to strike first.

259
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:43,467
That's what matters.

260
00:16:43,600 --> 00:16:45,200
You will now twist my hand.

261
00:16:46,633 --> 00:16:47,600
Towards that way.

262
00:16:48,867 --> 00:16:50,033
Hold the shoulder.

263
00:16:51,267 --> 00:16:54,867
Again, feel your anger.

264
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:57,267
And strike my side.

265
00:16:57,400 --> 00:16:58,500
Go!

266
00:16:59,733 --> 00:17:00,767
Yes.

267
00:17:02,067 --> 00:17:05,067
Now, I'll get your hand.

268
00:17:06,333 --> 00:17:10,567
But you counter it
by elbowing my side.

269
00:17:12,033 --> 00:17:13,833
Not a weak strike.

270
00:17:13,967 --> 00:17:16,200
You have to surprise me with it.

271
00:17:16,367 --> 00:17:18,433
One that is really strong.

272
00:17:18,567 --> 00:17:22,267
You won't give your opponent
a chance to react to your moves.

273
00:17:22,400 --> 00:17:29,800
Remember, a war is a mind game.
And you must strike first.

274
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:32,367
Go.

275
00:17:40,567 --> 00:17:41,633
What if she doesn't let go?

276
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:44,733
Good question.

277
00:17:44,867 --> 00:17:51,033
You will introduce your elbow
to her jaw or nose

278
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:53,933
to expose her weakness.

279
00:17:54,067 --> 00:17:55,567
This is where it goes.

280
00:17:57,967 --> 00:17:59,033
Ready?

281
00:18:00,533 --> 00:18:01,500
Go.

282
00:18:03,867 --> 00:18:04,933
Good.

283
00:18:08,300 --> 00:18:10,833
It's a bit hot today, isn't it?

284
00:18:10,967 --> 00:18:11,667
- Super.
- Mookie.

285
00:18:14,167 --> 00:18:15,333
I'm outta here.

286
00:18:15,467 --> 00:18:16,600
Mookie, wait.

287
00:18:18,667 --> 00:18:22,333
Look, I'm sorry
if I've offended you in any way.

288
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:24,567
It wasn't my intention
to hurt you.

289
00:18:24,700 --> 00:18:26,333
I'm only concerned about you.

290
00:18:26,467 --> 00:18:27,767
About everything
that's happening to you.

291
00:18:29,067 --> 00:18:30,700
Are you here to lecture me

292
00:18:30,833 --> 00:18:34,167
because I had a fight
with Stacy?

293
00:18:34,300 --> 00:18:35,833
You should've just ignored her.

294
00:18:37,167 --> 00:18:38,500
See?

295
00:18:38,633 --> 00:18:40,833
I knew it.

296
00:18:40,967 --> 00:18:41,867
You know what, Zayn?

297
00:18:43,300 --> 00:18:45,233
I don't need your scolding.

298
00:18:47,033 --> 00:18:48,033
I can take care of myself.

299
00:18:49,267 --> 00:18:51,567
We better stop being friends

300
00:18:51,700 --> 00:18:53,867
because the old Mookie
won't return anymore.

301
00:18:58,333 --> 00:18:59,867
What happened?

302
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:02,533
Mookie's shift in attitude
is unbelievable.

303
00:19:02,667 --> 00:19:04,933
I didn't expect that.

304
00:19:05,067 --> 00:19:06,900
I think I'm just gonna give her
some space.

305
00:19:08,733 --> 00:19:11,033
But, Zayn, please.

306
00:19:11,167 --> 00:19:13,100
Help me watch over Mookie.

307
00:19:13,233 --> 00:19:15,367
I heard Stacy and her friends
talking earlier.

308
00:19:16,700 --> 00:19:18,967
They're planning something bad
again against Mookie.

309
00:19:19,100 --> 00:19:20,567
- What?
- Yes.

310
00:19:20,700 --> 00:19:21,567
So, please.

311
00:19:21,700 --> 00:19:22,733
Please.

312
00:19:22,867 --> 00:19:25,200
Don't avoid her. Please help me
watch over her, okay?

313
00:19:30,133 --> 00:19:31,867
Now that you gained
the advantage,

314
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:33,467
you'll try to escape.

315
00:19:35,533 --> 00:19:39,133
Just as you turn,
Jade will stop you.

316
00:19:41,833 --> 00:19:43,267
When you turn your back,

317
00:19:44,700 --> 00:19:48,267
there's a good chance
that she will choke you.

318
00:19:53,533 --> 00:19:54,567
If that happens,

319
00:19:55,733 --> 00:20:02,733
you will use the back of your
head to hit her on the nose.

320
00:20:02,900 --> 00:20:04,700
That will be your target.

321
00:20:10,667 --> 00:20:11,667
Let's try.

322
00:20:12,967 --> 00:20:14,033
Here.

323
00:20:14,167 --> 00:20:15,300
Choke.

324
00:20:15,433 --> 00:20:16,867
Look down.

325
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:18,000
Hit me.

326
00:20:19,767 --> 00:20:24,433
And once you're free
and try to escape again,

327
00:20:24,567 --> 00:20:26,900
she'll hold on to your hair.

328
00:20:27,033 --> 00:20:28,200
Do it now.

329
00:20:29,833 --> 00:20:32,267
That's where you'll turn around.

330
00:20:36,467 --> 00:20:37,133
Good.

331
00:20:39,633 --> 00:20:40,633
Very good.

332
00:20:52,333 --> 00:20:53,267
Very good.

333
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:06,300
Logan, thank you so much.

334
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:10,167
Anytime.

335
00:21:11,300 --> 00:21:15,100
Just remember, the fight
isn't just physical.

336
00:21:17,233 --> 00:21:19,167
It's about using your mind.

337
00:21:19,300 --> 00:21:24,233
You need to have determination
to win your battle.

338
00:21:26,233 --> 00:21:30,367
Every punch you throw,
be it a jab or a kick,

339
00:21:32,133 --> 00:21:33,967
must come from within.

340
00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:41,667
So you can show
what you're fighting for.

341
00:21:48,033 --> 00:21:51,267
Mookie is my reason
to fight Jade.

342
00:22:05,933 --> 00:22:08,133
Jade, I'd like you
to meet Altair.

343
00:22:08,267 --> 00:22:10,967
He's an excellent private
investigator.

344
00:22:11,100 --> 00:22:12,067
Trusted.

345
00:22:16,533 --> 00:22:18,167
Her name is Emma Joseco.

346
00:22:19,433 --> 00:22:20,400
She was last seen

347
00:22:20,533 --> 00:22:22,967
in Havenwood Psychiatry
Sanctuary last year

348
00:22:23,100 --> 00:22:24,467
before she escaped.

349
00:22:24,600 --> 00:22:27,867
All the information you need
is in that envelope.

350
00:22:32,567 --> 00:22:34,600
Give me five days to find her.

351
00:22:36,333 --> 00:22:39,533
I thought your private
investigator was good.

352
00:22:39,667 --> 00:22:40,633
Three days.

353
00:22:41,767 --> 00:22:43,033
And I'll find Emma Joseco.

354
00:22:44,667 --> 00:22:46,233
Why are you looking for Emma?

355
00:22:53,167 --> 00:22:54,433
What's your plan for her?

356
00:22:57,700 --> 00:23:01,500
Love, this is Leticia,
my long-lost best friend.

357
00:23:01,633 --> 00:23:04,300
- This is Danilo.
- Hello. Nice to meet you.

358
00:23:04,433 --> 00:23:06,967
I'm looking for Emma
because...

359
00:23:08,800 --> 00:23:11,233
no matter what you say,
she's still my sister.

360
00:23:12,733 --> 00:23:15,400
Even though she abandoned you
and Mookie.

361
00:23:17,300 --> 00:23:22,033
I only want to know
if she's okay, happy,

362
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:25,533
healthy, or already
content with someone else.

363
00:23:25,667 --> 00:23:28,233
I don't know.
I just want closure.

364
00:23:28,367 --> 00:23:30,533
That's all I want.

365
00:23:30,667 --> 00:23:32,433
Jade, don't.

366
00:23:33,933 --> 00:23:37,333
She has no intention
of coming back to us.

367
00:23:37,467 --> 00:23:38,767
We're just wasting our time.

368
00:23:40,933 --> 00:23:42,033
Just let her be.

369
00:23:56,533 --> 00:23:57,300
So what now?

370
00:23:58,933 --> 00:24:00,633
You will still find Emma.

371
00:24:02,933 --> 00:24:06,800
What do I do next
once I find Emma?

372
00:24:10,133 --> 00:24:12,233
Are you really just a private
investigator?

373
00:24:14,067 --> 00:24:16,733
He's not only a good
investigator.

374
00:24:17,967 --> 00:24:19,033
He's also a good...

375
00:24:20,300 --> 00:24:21,300
hitman.

376
00:24:24,100 --> 00:24:25,167
Good.

377
00:24:26,933 --> 00:24:31,267
Once you find Emma,
I want you to get rid of her.

378
00:24:32,500 --> 00:24:34,433
She gets in the way of my plans.

379
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:39,933
Besides, Mookie only has one
mother.

380
00:24:41,567 --> 00:24:42,800
And that's me.

381
00:25:13,700 --> 00:25:14,667
Is anyone there?

382
00:25:30,100 --> 00:25:31,233
Hey!

383
00:25:31,367 --> 00:25:33,000
Let go of me! Who are you?

384
00:25:41,700 --> 00:25:43,067
Emma's not coming back.

385
00:25:44,333 --> 00:25:46,633
She went with another man.

386
00:25:46,767 --> 00:25:48,400
- What?
- What?

387
00:25:48,533 --> 00:25:51,567
That's what the private
investigator found out.

388
00:25:51,700 --> 00:25:56,000
That's why it's about time
we accept

389
00:25:56,133 --> 00:25:59,700
that Emma's never
coming back ever.

390
00:25:59,833 --> 00:26:01,667
Emma's dead.

391
00:26:01,800 --> 00:26:02,667
What?

392
00:26:02,800 --> 00:26:03,833
Mom!

393
00:26:05,600 --> 00:26:06,667
This is where I buried her.

394
00:26:06,800 --> 00:26:08,433
Tell me, Altair.

395
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:10,467
How did you kill Emma?

396
00:26:10,600 --> 00:26:14,967
I covered her head with plastic
until she ran out of breath.

397
00:26:15,100 --> 00:26:16,267
I hope...

398
00:26:19,200 --> 00:26:24,000
That you rot in hell.
